# Ask Before Workaround

When blocked by missing credentials, insufficient permissions, or a required manual action — **stop and ask the user** rather than attempting workarounds.

## Rule

If a task requires:
- An API key or token you don't have
- A permission level beyond what's been provided
- A manual action in an external dashboard (e.g. Supabase SQL editor, AWS console, Vercel)
- A CLI tool that isn't installed

**Do not:**
- Try alternative endpoints hoping one works
- Build temporary shims or one-off routes to bypass the gap
- Silently skip the step and move on

**Do:**
- State exactly what is blocking you
- Explain what credential/action/tool is needed and why
- Provide the exact SQL, command, or config for the user to run themselves
- Wait for confirmation before proceeding

## Example

❌ BAD — trying 4 different API endpoints hoping one accepts the wrong key type

✅ GOOD:
> "I can't create the Supabase table via the REST API — that requires DDL which PostgREST doesn't support. Please run this SQL in your [Supabase SQL Editor](https://supabase.com/dashboard/project/_/sql/new) and let me know when done:"
> ```sql
> CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS ...
> ```
